  "text": "anchor RSP's office is located in the Grain Belt Brewery - Bottling House. Image: Google Maps The Minnesota Star Tribune is reporting on a strange case involving the former principal of Minneapolis-based RSP Architects \u0026 Planners after he filed a lawsuit alleging retaliation in response to his apparent discovery of missing funds. The employee in question, Todd Novak, claims he notified senior leadership that there was between $2-6 million absent from its balance sheets while in the process of applying internally for a CEO position.  The outlet says: \"The suit accuses RSP of retaliation in violation of the Minnesota Whistleblower Act and seeks unspecified compensation for loss of income, mental anguish, emotional distress and other financial and emotional loss.\"  Novak was later laid off in a cost-saving move in March. Another caveat, per the Star Tribune: \"The missing funds mattered for several reasons, including that RSP ran an employee stock ownership plan that was funded based on company profits.\" Similar articles on Archinect that may interest you... Gaudi's Sagrada Familia fined $41 million for lack of building permit New York State Man Faces Up to 15 Years for Practicing Architecture Without Being Licensed or Registered Harvard withdraws acceptance offers from students who created offensive memes Alejandro Zaera-Polo has been removed from his faculty position as Princeton continues its row with the former SoA dean Suspected Long Island serial killer Rex Heuermann was a Manhattan-based architect Drones for Architects: New Capabilities for the Construction Sector, How to Get Started and How to Navigate the Law",
