d-millions-missing/601159470\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eMinnesota Star Tribune\u003c/a\u003e \u003c/em\u003eis reporting on a strange case involving the former principal of Minneapolis-based \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/firms/cover/34031964/rsp-architects-planners-engineers\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eRSP Architects \u0026amp; Planners\u003c/a\u003e after he filed a lawsuit alleging retaliation in response to his apparent discovery of missing funds. The employee in question, Todd Novak, claims he notified senior leadership that there was between $2-6 million absent from its balance sheets while in the process of applying internally for a CEO position. \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe outlet says: \u0026#34;The suit accuses RSP of retaliation in violation of the Minnesota Whistleblower Act and seeks unspecified compensation for loss of income, mental anguish, emotional distress and other financial and emotional loss.\u0026#34; \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNovak was later laid off in a cost-saving move in March. Another caveat, per the \u003cem\u003eStar Tribune\u003c/em\u003e: \u0026#34;The missing funds mattered for several reasons, including that RSP ran an employee stock ownership plan that was funded based on company profits.\u0026#34;\u003c/p\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cbr clear=\"all\"/\u003e\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\t\u003ch2\u003eSimilar articles on Archinect that may interest you...\u003c/h2\u003e\n\t\t\u003cul\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cli\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/news/article/150091637/gaudi-s-sagrada-familia-fined-41-million-for-lack-of-building-permit\" title=\"Gaudi\u0026#39;s Sagrada Familia fined $41 million for lack of building permit \"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t